it.emarolab.owloop.core

Interface ObjectProperty.Range<O,J,Y>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the type of ontology in which the axioms for classes will be applied.
    J - the type of the described class.
    Y - the type of restriction of the range of the defined property. (it represents the of Semantic.Axioms managed by this Descriptor.
    All Superinterfaces:
    ObjectProperty<O,J>, Semantic, Semantic.Descriptor<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MORObjectProperty.Range
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MORDomainObjectProperty, MORFullObjectProperty
    Enclosing interface:
    ObjectProperty<O,J>

    public static interface ObjectProperty.Range<O,J,Y>
extends ObjectProperty<O,J>
    The Semantic.Descriptor for the definition of an ontological object property range.

    This Semantic.Descriptor synchronises the definition of a specific object property range (i.e.: the Ground#getGroundInstance()). Definition is defined as conjunction of restriction properties that creates classes in the range of the described property. More in details, such a restriction can be of the type:

    • class restriction: a range is restricted to a class.
    • data restriction: a range is defined to have data properties into a given range. It is also possible to describe the cardinality of this restriction to be: existential (some), universal (all), minimal, maximal and exact.
    • object restriction: a range is defined to have object properties into a given class. It is also possible to describe the cardinality of this restriction to be: existential (some), universal (all), minimal, maximal and exact.
    This description is not considered from an OOP point of view (it is not possible to build them) since their are not entities that fall back in the Semantic representations.
